The Chronicle Mthabisi Tshuma, Showbiz Correspondent KE Yona TV has unveiled three presenters who will be the face of their educational shows as content production is expected to commence in June. The presenters are John Mudau, Modesta Mafunga and Wenzile Mhlanga. Ke Yona TV Executive Communications Officer Vuyelwa Sibindi announced the appointments and said they wish the trio a successful trail in the fast growing television station that was licensed last year. <img class="wp-image-530249 size-full" src="https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2021/02/Wenzile-Mhlanga.jpg" alt="" width="680" height="380" srcset="https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2021/02/Wenzile-Mhlanga.jpg 680w, https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2021/02/Wenzile-Mhlanga-360x200.jpg 360w" sizes="(max-width: 680px) 100vw, 680px" /> Wenzile Mhlanga “KeYona Television wishes to announce that it has selected John Mudau, Modesta Mafunga and Wenzile Mhlanga to present its education shows. KeYona Television wishes them the best on this new journey,” said Sibindi. John Mudau is a humanitarian worker by profession with vast experience in disaster response and development management. He is well travelled and fluent in five Zimbabwean indigenous languages and has been in the education sector for a number of years. Mudau has a passion for broadcasting and acting. Mafunga is a lady who is passionate about community development projects and has invested her days in voluntary work. She is also media and broadcasting fanatic who is keen to learn and explore in the industry. <img class="wp-image-530251 size-full" src="https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2021/02/Modesta-Mafunga.jpg" alt="" width="680" height="380" srcset="https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2021/02/Modesta-Mafunga.jpg 680w, https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2021/02/Modesta-Mafunga-360x200.jpg 360w" sizes="(max-width: 680px) 100vw, 680px" /> Modesta Mafunga As for Mhlanga she is a Fingers modelling school graduate, former Miss Tourism Bulawayo and former Dreams to Fame presenter and MC. Mhlanga is also an event organiser/manager, coordinator for Yiskhathi Sethu and has initiated and hosted modelling competitions in primary schools around the city of Bulawayo. She is also a book publisher and production editor. – @mthabisi_mthire